dsxT3E3MIB.name: dsxT3E3MIB
dsxT3E3MIB.contactinfo: Tiara Networks Customer Support 525 Race Street, Suite 100, San Jose, CA 95126 USA Tel: +1 408-216-4700 Fax: +1 408-216-4701 Email: support@tiaranetworks.com
dsxT3E3MIB.description: Interface MIB definitions for Tiara T3/E3 interface modules.

dsxT3E3IfConfigLineTable.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigLineTable
dsxT3E3IfConfigLineTable.description: A list of T3/E3 interfaces currently configured.

dsxT3E3IfConfigLineEntry.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigLineEntry
dsxT3E3IfConfigLineEntry.description: An entry containing configuration information for each currently active T3/E3 interface.

dsxT3E3IfIndex.name: dsxT3E3IfIndex
dsxT3E3IfIndex.description: An integer value that is an index to the entries of ifTable (MIB-II) whose interface type is ds3.

dsxT3E3IfConfigLineType.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigLineType
dsxT3E3IfConfigLineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of T3/E3 C-bit or E3 application implementing this interface. The type of interface affects the interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The rate of T3/E3 is 44.736 Mbps and E3 is 34.368 Mbps. The values, in sequence, describe: linetype-m13 ANSI T1.107-1988 linetype-cbitparity ANSI T1.107a-1990

dsxT3E3IfConfigLineCode.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigLineCode
dsxT3E3IfConfigLineCode.description: This variable describes the variety of zero code suppression used on this interface, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. linecode-B3ZS and linecode-HDB3 refer to the use of specified patterns of normal bits and bipolar violations that are used to replace sequences of zero bits of a specified length.

dsxT3E3IfConfigCableLength.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigCableLength
dsxT3E3IfConfigCableLength.description: The length of the T3/E3 line in feet. This object provides information for line build out circuitry if it exists and can use this object to adjust the line build out.

dsxT3E3IfConfigTransmitClock.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigTransmitClock
dsxT3E3IfConfigTransmitClock.description: The source of transmit clock. It is derived from the recovered receive clock of another T3/E3 interface.

dsxT3E3IfConfigDS3ScramblingEnable.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigDS3ScramblingEnable
dsxT3E3IfConfigDS3ScramblingEnable.description: To enable or disable scrambling. This is applicable only to clear channel TE3.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlTable.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlTable
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlTable.description: A list of T3/E3 interfaces currently configured.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlEntry.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlEntry
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlEntry.description: An entry containing configuration for each currently active T3/E3 interface.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlEIC.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlEIC
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlEIC.description: The equipment identification code (up to 10 characters) describes a specific piece of equipment.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlLIC.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlLIC
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlLIC.description: The location identification code (up to 11 characters) describes a specific location.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlFIC.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlFIC
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlFIC.description: The frame identification code (up to 10 charaters) identifies where the equipment is located within a building at a given location.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlUIC.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlUIC
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlUIC.description: A code (up to 6 characters) that identifies the equipment location within a bay.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlPFI.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlPFI
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlPFI.description: The facility identification code (up to 38 characters) identifies a specific T3/E3 path.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlPort.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlPort
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlPort.description: The Port number is the designation of equipment, port that initiates the idle signal.

dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlGenerator.name: dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlGenerator
dsxT3E3IfConfigMdlGenerator.description: Gen No. is the number of the signal generator that initiates the test signal.

dsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleType.description: Sampling type for the threshold alarm.

dsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigStartupType.name: dsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigStartupType
dsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigStartupType.description: Startup Type for the threashold alarm.

dsxT3E3IfTestConfigType.name: dsxT3E3IfTestConfigType
dsxT3E3IfTestConfigType.description: Test type for the TE3 interface. Only TestType is mandatory to perform no-test, payload-loopback-test, or line-loopback-test. ConfigLoopCode is mandatory to perform remote-lpup-test and remote-lpdn-test.

dsxT3E3IfStatusLineStatus.name: dsxT3E3IfStatusLineStatus
dsxT3E3IfStatusLineStatus.description: Line Status of the T3/E3 interface. sendPattern - TRUE if the line transmiting bit pattern, sendTE3Code - sending T3/E3 code, sendResetCode - transmits Reset Code if it is TRUE, sendPayloadcode - transmits the payload code, sendLinecode - transmitts the line code, febe - Far End Block Error, pde - pulse Density code transmission, lorc - loss of recieve clock, rfebe - recieve far end block error, ris - recieve Idle signal, rexz - recieve exessive zeros, rcvTestCode - recieve test code, loopback - loopback status , rlos - recieve loss of signal, rlof - recieve loss of frame, tais - transmit alarm indication signal, rais - recieve alarm indication signal, trai - transmit remote alarm indication, rrai - recieve remote alarm indication,

dsxT3E3IfStatusTransmitClock.name: dsxT3E3IfStatusTransmitClock
dsxT3E3IfStatusTransmitClock.description: The source of tranmit clock. 'timing-line' indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'timing-internal' indicates that a local clock source is used.

dsxT3E3IfStatusYellowLED.name: dsxT3E3IfStatusYellowLED

dsxT3E3IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus.name: dsxT3E3IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus
dsxT3E3IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus.description: Current status of all the T3/E3 interface alarms. RRAI - Recieve Remote Alarm Indication, TRAI - Transmit Remote Alarm Indication, TAIS - Transmit Alarm Indication Siganl, RLOF - Recieve Loss Of Frame, RLOS - Recieve Loss Of Sync, Loopback - Status of Loop back, rcvTestCode - Recieve Test Code, rblu - Recieve Blue Alarm, RIS - Recieve Idle Signal, REXZ - Recieve Excessive Zeros, RFBE - Recieve Frame Bit Error, RPE - Recieve Parity Error, RCPE - Recieve C-Parity Error, LORC - Loss Of Recive Clock (LORC), TPDE - transmit pulse density, RAIS - Recieve Alarm Indication Signal, TFEBE - Transmit Far End Block Alarm.
